<div class=3D"w3-panel ws-note">
<p><strong>What is the difference between PX, EM and Percent?</strong></p><=
p>Pixel=20
is a static measurement, while percent and EM are relative=20
measurements. Percent depends on its parent font size. EM is relative to th=
e=20
  current font size of the element (2em means 2 times the size of the curre=
nt=20
  font). So, If the font=20
size of body is 16 pixels, then 150% will be 24 pixels (1.5 * 16), and 2em =
will=20
  be 32 pixels (16 * 2).=20
Look at <a href=3D"https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_units.php">CSS Unit=
s</a> for more=20
measurement units.</p>
</div>



